race.comment: Looks a race in two and the leaning is to ITSUKUSHIMA (2). He keeps racing well but frustratingly just continues to find one better, finishing runner up in his past four, with an aggregate beaten margin of just 1.3 lengths in those defeats. He'll roll forward from the wide gate and take plenty of catching. PRIVATE JUMBO (1) is the clear danger. He dropped back to this grade at Sale and ran a good race up on speed, just finding one better by a length. He'll look to make ITSUKUSHIMA work early and that could prove the difference. CHANTRA (11) took her maiden second up at Colac with a tough win. This is a fair bit harder but she's open to improvement. FLAG FLYER (8) is going well this time in and maps for a soft trail behind a strong speed. SO SUAVE (5) can improve off a poor showing first up.
